<paragraph blockId="4.[159,762,854,1405]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Measurements — Idiosoma L 792, W 567; dorsal shield L 663, W 459, L/W ratio 1.44; dorsal plate L 606; shoulder plate L 150 – 156, W 73 – 75, L/W ratio 2.0-2.1; frontal plate L 130 – 131, W 72 – 74, L/W ratio 1.76 – 1.8; L shoulder/frontal plate ratio 1.15 – 1.2. Gnathosomal bay L 141, Cx-I total L 256, Cx-I mL 116, Cx-II+III mL 54; ratio Cx-I L/Cx- II+III mL 2.21; Cx-I mL/Cx-II+III mL 4.8. Genital field L/W 156/146, ratio 1.07; egg maximum diameter 203; distance genital field-excretory pore 209, genital field-caudal idiosoma margin 325. Chelicera total L 208; palp total L 185, dL/H, dL/H ratio: P- 1, 26/25, 1.07; P-2, 54/39, 1.4; P-3, 39/32, 1.22; P- 4, 46/23, 2.0; P-5, 20/11, 1.9; L P-2/P-4 ratio 1.17. Legs: dL of I-L-4–6: 102, 103, 103; I-L-6 H 84, dL/H I-L-6 ratio 1.22.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[159,762,1434,1949]" lastBlockId="4.[826,1429,311,650]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">
Remarks — The single female from 
<collectingCountry box="[662,761,1434,1458]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
resembles superficially specimens tentatively included in the so-called 
<taxonomicName authority="(K. Viets, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macroporus">
<emphasis box="[461,633,1504,1527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. macroporus</emphasis>
(K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets K." pageId="4" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref16928" refString="Viets K. 1935 - Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda-Expedition - Arch. Hydrobiol., Suppl. 13, Trop. Binnengewasser, 5 (3): 484 - 594, 5 (4): 595 - 738, Suppl. 14, Trop. Binnengewasser, 6 (1): 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
-complex (see Wiles 1991, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesi'c V. &amp; Smit H." box="[525,758,1539,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 27" refId="ref16237" refString="Pesi'c V., Smit H. 2009 - Water mites of the family Torrenticolidae Piersig, 1902 (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from Thailand, Part II. The genus Monatractides K. Viets - Zootaxa, 2012: 1 - 27." type="journal article" year="2009">Peši´c and Smit 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesi'c V. &amp; Smit H." box="[159,231,1574,1598]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref16413" refString="Pesi'c V., Smit H. 2014 b - Torrenticolid water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Torrenticolidae) from Malaysian Borneo - Zootaxa, 3840 (1): 1 - 72" type="journal article" year="2014">2014b</bibRefCitation>
). This group includes several similar species known from SE Asia, 
<emphasis box="[410,440,1610,1633]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">i.e.</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walter, 1928)" baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[453,762,1609,1633]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis box="[453,598,1609,1633]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. angulatus</emphasis>
(Walter, 1928)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[167,232,1644,1668]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">India</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(K. Viets, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[260,634,1644,1668]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macroporus">
<emphasis box="[260,430,1645,1668]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. macroporus</emphasis>
(K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets K." box="[492,626,1644,1668]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref16928" refString="Viets K. 1935 - Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda-Expedition - Arch. Hydrobiol., Suppl. 13, Trop. Binnengewasser, 5 (3): 484 - 594, 5 (4): 595 - 738, Suppl. 14, Trop. Binnengewasser, 6 (1): 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(Sumatra, Java, Borneo), 
<taxonomicName authority="(K. Viets, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[337,634,1679,1703]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[337,441,1680,1703]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. major</emphasis>
(K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets K." box="[496,626,1679,1703]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref16928" refString="Viets K. 1935 - Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda-Expedition - Arch. Hydrobiol., Suppl. 13, Trop. Binnengewasser, 5 (3): 484 - 594, 5 (4): 595 - 738, Suppl. 14, Trop. Binnengewasser, 6 (1): 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(Java), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Viets, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. longiventris</emphasis>
(Viets, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
(Java, Borneo), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lundblad, 1941)" baseAuthorityName="Lundblad" baseAuthorityYear="1941" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tranversalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. tranversalis</emphasis>
(Lundblad, 1941)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[490,610,1749,1773]" name="Myanmar" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Cook, 1966)" baseAuthorityName="Cook" baseAuthorityYear="1966" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nondescripta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. nondescripta</emphasis>
(Cook, 1966)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[415,480,1784,1808]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">India</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiles, 1991" authorityName="Wiles" authorityYear="1991" box="[505,761,1784,1808]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[505,613,1785,1808]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. minor</emphasis>
Wiles, 1991
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[167,275,1819,1843]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2014" box="[344,455,1819,1843]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiales">
<emphasis box="[344,455,1819,1843]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. epiales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Pesi'c V. &amp; Smit H." box="[462,695,1819,1843]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref16413" refString="Pesi'c V., Smit H. 2014 b - Torrenticolid water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Torrenticolidae) from Malaysian Borneo - Zootaxa, 3840 (1): 1 - 72" type="journal article" year="2014">Peši´c &amp; Smit, 2014b</bibRefCitation>
(Borneo). The specimen from our study differs in less narrower gnathosomal bay and somewhat shorter P-4 (L P-4/P-3 ratio ≈ 1.2). In this character state, it agrees with 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiles, 1991" authorityName="Wiles" authorityYear="1991" box="[996,1242,311,335]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis box="[996,1101,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">M. minor</emphasis>
Wiles, 1991
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1316,1425,311,335]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="396">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, a species differing in minor idiosoma and palp dimensions and four dorsoglandularia on the dorsal plate (Wiles 1991). Understanding the taxonomic position of the species of this complex species is not possible without the application of molecular techniques (
<bibRefCitation author="Pesi'c V. &amp; Smit H." box="[917,1166,521,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref16413" refString="Pesi'c V., Smit H. 2014 b - Torrenticolid water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Torrenticolidae) from Malaysian Borneo - Zootaxa, 3840 (1): 1 - 72" type="journal article" year="2014">Peši´c and Smit 2014b</bibRefCitation>
), so introducing a new species on basis of a female will create more confusion given the present state of knowledge of this species.
</paragraph>
